Sentencas: A dense BaCe0.8Sm0.2O5+delta (BCS) electrolyte was fabricated on a porous anode by in situ drop-coating to develop a simple and cost-effective route to fabricate proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Layered SmBaCuCoO5+δ and SmBaCuFeO5+δ perovskite oxides as cathode materials for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: Layered perovskite-structure oxides SmBaCuCoO5+delta (SBCC) and SmBaCuFeO5+delta (SBCF) were prepared and the electrical conductivity, the thermal expansion coefficient and electrochemical performance were investigated as potential cathode materials for proton-conducting SOFCs.
Titulo: Layered SmBaCuCoO5+δ and SmBaCuFeO5+δ perovskite oxides as cathode materials for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficients of SBCC and SBCF were suitable for BCS electrolyte and the electrical conductivity of the SBCC is higher than that of the SBCF.
Titulo: Layered SmBaCuCoO5+δ and SmBaCuFeO5+δ perovskite oxides as cathode materials for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: The maximum power density of 449 mW cm(2) and 333 mW cm(2) at 700 degrees C were obtained for the SBCC/BCS/NiO-BCS and SBCF/BCS/NiO-BCS cells, respectively.
Titulo: Layered SmBaCuCoO5+δ and SmBaCuFeO5+δ perovskite oxides as cathode materials for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: The interfacial polarization resistances for SBCC and SBCF cathode are as low as 0.137 Omega cm(-2) and 0.196 Omega cm(-2) at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Layered SmBaCuCoO5+δ and SmBaCuFeO5+δ perovskite oxides as cathode materials for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: The results indicate that the SBCC and SBCF are promising cathode materials for proton-conducting SOFCs.
Titulo: Layered SmBaCuCoO5+δ and SmBaCuFeO5+δ perovskite oxides as cathode materials for proton-conducting SOFCs
